Smart Makers Operations System
MVP Technical Blueprint v1.1
Operational Tightening Addendum

1. Operational Philosophy
The system is built around:
Management By Exception
The manager should not need to manually monitor everything constantly.
The system exists to surface:
operational deviations
missing reports
unresolved shortages
incomplete lesson closures
upcoming operational risks
group progression issues
scheduling concerns
If everything is operating correctly:
 the system should feel quiet.
The dashboard should emphasize:
attention, not data overload.

2. Unified Operational Flag System
The MVP should internally treat operational problems as:
Flags
Flags are the core operational control mechanism of the system.
Flags may appear:
in the Attention Queue
on Lesson Pages
on Group Pages
on Dashboard cards

Initial MVP Flags
Lesson Flags
Missing Attendance
Missing Summary
Lesson Closed With Exception
Instructor Replaced
Cancelled Lesson Requires Follow-Up

Group Flags
Group Off Planned Progress
Missing Planned Model
Group Requires Syllabus Review

Materials Flags
Open Shortage
Upcoming Material Risk

Operational Flags
Open Operational Task
Upcoming Scheduling Risk

3. Minimal Audit Requirements
The MVP does NOT require enterprise audit logging.
However:
 basic operational traceability is required.

Required Audit Fields
All operational entities should include:
created_at
updated_at
updated_by

Lesson-Specific Audit Fields
Lessons should additionally include:
closed_at
closed_by
exception_closed_at
exception_reason

Important Principle
The system should preserve:
operational accountability
basic debugging capability
historical visibility
without introducing heavy audit infrastructure.

4. Group Alignment Visibility
One of the core operational loops is:
Group Alignment
The system must allow the manager to identify:
groups progressing slower than planned
groups progressing differently than planned
groups with inconsistent stage progression

MVP Requirement
The system should compare:
Planned
vs.
Actual
for:
model
lesson number
stage number

Visibility Rule
The system does NOT automatically correct syllabus progression.
The system only:
surfaces deviations
allows the manager to intervene manually

Suggested Dashboard Section
Groups Requiring Alignment Review
Examples:
Actual model differs from planned model
Actual stage significantly behind planned stage
Group repeatedly deviates from syllabus

5. Upcoming Operational Risk Visibility
The system should not only react to problems after they happen.
The MVP should also surface:
Upcoming Operational Risks

Examples
Upcoming lesson with open shortage
Upcoming lesson with missing planned model
Upcoming lesson without assigned instructor
Upcoming lesson following unresolved cancellation
Upcoming lesson with unresolved exception flag

Important Constraint
This is NOT predictive AI.
This is simple operational visibility.

6. Mobile-First Operational Constraint
The MVP is intended primarily for:
managers in the field
mobile usage
fast operational interaction

Required Mobile Capabilities
The manager must comfortably be able to:
open dashboard
open lesson
mark attendance received
close lesson
close lesson with exception
create shortage
create operational task
copy WhatsApp templates
from a phone browser.

UX Principle
The system should prioritize:
fast taps
low cognitive load
large interaction targets
checklist-style workflows
over:
dense tables
desktop-heavy interfaces

7. Source of Truth Definition
For the MVP:
Manager Input Inside The System Is The Operational Source Of Truth

Clarifications
WhatsApp conversations are not authoritative records
External spreadsheets are not authoritative records
PlanDo is external operational context only
The dashboard reflects the system state only

Operational Principle
If information exists only in WhatsApp,
 it is considered:
not operationally secured.

8. Instructor Lesson Summary (Not Payroll)
The MVP does NOT contain a true payroll system.
The payroll-related screen should internally be treated as:
Instructor Lesson Summary
Purpose:
operational verification
lesson count validation
estimated payout visibility

The MVP Does NOT Include
invoices
payroll exports
travel calculations
bonuses
tax calculations
payslips

9. Pilot Constraints
The MVP is intentionally constrained.

Initial Pilot Assumptions
1 Admin
1 Manager
low operational volume
no instructor login
no mobile app
no offline support
no external integrations
no advanced inventory system
no advanced scheduling engine
no automation-heavy workflows
no AI prediction systems

Important Principle
Complexity should only be added:
 after operational validation.

10. Pilot Success Metrics
The pilot succeeds if:
the manager checks the dashboard daily
lessons stop falling through the cracks
missing attendance becomes consistently visible
missing summaries are reduced
shortages become visible before lessons
operational follow-up becomes centralized
WhatsApp follow-up becomes standardized
group progression becomes operationally visible
the manager feels reduced operational stress

11. MVP Architectural Philosophy
The MVP should prioritize:
operational clarity
simplicity
speed of implementation
workflow stability
low training overhead
over:
elegance
automation
enterprise scalability
advanced optimization

12. Future Expansion Philosophy
The MVP should preserve the ability to later add:
instructor-facing workflows
inventory systems
automated messaging
advanced scheduling
franchise management
analytics
integrations
However:
Future scalability must not increase MVP complexity unnecessarily.
The MVP must remain:
aggressively operational-first.


